{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"947b95e0-3958-446c-89de-e481f0aecb54","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nCheck the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any API or behavioral changes that may affect your app. Also update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ee02d4ac-b3a8-473a-9798-a4b3336707d0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question about upgrading .NET versions — I don't need to search any codebase since they described their setup. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":327,"requestId":"7032:2657B6:5EDDB0F:66BB190:69FBEE48"},"id":"848b53c1-3bb1-449a-afc6-f3878e0b1d40","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:43:43.027Z","parentId":"b0891726-6d80-48d3-b944-2d83354f11a1"}
